{"title_page": "Real Boys", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|1998 book by William S. Pollack}}\n\n{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] -->\n| name          = Real Boys: Rescuing Our Sons from the Myths of Boyhood\n| image         = File:Real Boys.jpg\n| caption       = Cover of the first edition \n| author        = William S. Pollack\n| illustrator   = \n| cover_artist  = \n| country       = United States\n| language      = English\n| series        = \n| subject       = [[Boy|Boyhood]]\n| publisher     = Owl Books\n| release_date  = 1998\n| media_type    = Print ([[Paperback]])\n| pages         = 480\n| isbn          = 978-0805061833\n| preceded_by   = \n| followed_by   = \n}}\n\n'''''Real Boys: Rescuing Our Sons from the Myths of Boyhood''''' is a 1998 book about [[Boy|boyhood]] and boy culture by [[William S. Pollack]],<ref name=\"Accessola2 PDF\">http://www.accessola2.com/superconference2008/thu/409/tdsb.pdf</ref> in which the author asserts that toxic conceptions of [[masculinity]] in boy culture leads to boys doing poorly in [[education]] and health and having higher involvement in [[violent crime]]s and [[suicide]] than girls.\n\n==Background==\nPollack devoted more than 20 years to researching the material presented in the book.<ref>\"Real Boys, William Pollack, Book - Barnes & Noble.\" Barnes & Noble.com. Web. 23 August 2010. <http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Real-Boys/William-Pollack/e/9780805061833>.</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Real Boys'' became a best-seller.<ref>[[Sommers, Christina Hoff]]. ''The War Against Boys: How Misguided Feminism is Harming Our Young Men''. Simon & Schuster, 2000, 13.</ref> A Toronto District School Board review of the book says: \"Pollack's groundbreaking book has become the academic bible that the new boys' movement was launched from.\"<ref name=\"Accessola2 PDF\"/>\n\nThe philosopher [[Christina Hoff Sommers]], who attributes the book's popularity to the public response to the [[Columbine High School massacre]], writes that ''Real Boys'' is, \"The most popular book calling for the rescue of boys from the constraints of a harmful masculinity\".<ref>[[Sommers, Christina Hoff]]. ''The War Against Boys: How Misguided Feminism is Harming Our Young Men''. Simon & Schuster, 2000, 138, 230.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{parenting}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1998 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Child development]]\n[[Category:English-language books]]\n[[Category:Parenting books]]\n\n\n{{psych-book-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|1998 book by William S. Pollack}}\n\n{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] -->\n| name          = Real Boys: Rescuing Our Sons from the Myths of Boyhood\n| image         = File:Real Boys.jpg\n| caption       = Cover of the first edition \n| author        = William S. Pollack\n| illustrator   = \n| cover_artist  = \n| country       = United States\n| language      = English\n| series        = \n| subject       = [[Boyhood]]\n| publisher     = Owl Books\n| release_date  = 1998\n| media_type    = Print ([[Paperback]])\n| pages         = 480\n| isbn          = 978-0805061833\n| preceded_by   = \n| followed_by   = \n}}\n\n'''''Real Boys: Rescuing Our Sons from the Myths of Boyhood''''' is a 1998 book about [[boyhood]] and boy culture by [[William S. Pollack]],<ref name=\"Accessola2 PDF\">http://www.accessola2.com/superconference2008/thu/409/tdsb.pdf</ref> in which the author asserts that toxic conceptions of [[masculinity]] in boy culture leads to boys doing poorly in [[education]] and health and having higher involvement in [[violent crime]]s and [[suicide]] than girls.\n\n==Background==\nPollack devoted more than 20 years to researching the material presented in the book.<ref>\"Real Boys, William Pollack, Book - Barnes & Noble.\" Barnes & Noble.com. Web. 23 August 2010. <http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Real-Boys/William-Pollack/e/9780805061833>.</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Real Boys'' became a best-seller.<ref>[[Sommers, Christina Hoff]]. ''The War Against Boys: How Misguided Feminism is Harming Our Young Men''. Simon & Schuster, 2000, 13.</ref> A Toronto District School Board review of the book says: \"Pollack's groundbreaking book has become the academic bible that the new boys' movement was launched from.\"<ref name=\"Accessola2 PDF\"/>\n\nThe philosopher [[Christina Hoff Sommers]], who attributes the book's popularity to the public response to the [[Columbine High School massacre]], writes that ''Real Boys'' is, \"The most popular book calling for the rescue of boys from the constraints of a harmful masculinity\".<ref>[[Sommers, Christina Hoff]]. ''The War Against Boys: How Misguided Feminism is Harming Our Young Men''. Simon & Schuster, 2000, 138, 230.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{parenting}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1998 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Child development]]\n[[Category:English-language books]]\n[[Category:Parenting books]]\n\n\n{{psych-book-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toBoyhood(link changed toBoy; link changed toBoy) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_Boys"}
